2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper is concerned with the security of communication over a wiretap channel, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper involves solving a dual secret key agreement problem, which may involve computational complexity considerations. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The wiretap channel model may have applications in social and information networks, where secure communication is important. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The wiretap channel model may also have applications in multimedia communication, where secure transmission of audio and video data is important.
